The flavors are great, the location is amazing, and the price is fair compared to other restaurants in Tel Aviv.
The waitress was super nice but there was some general problems with the service and hospitality.
At the end- it really worth a visit.', 'rating': 3, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhu-e9PG1FRpcj5hIbUOSgYPR6z3dTcn5gNTfFEjFxBz064ivU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'Lidor Bracha', 'publishTime': '2022-10-17T09:51:46.857Z'}, {'text': 'Well, maybe my expectations were too high, but I read quite a few reviews which were positive so I had to give it a try, and unfortunately it wasnâ€™t as good as I thought it would be.
The pizza was very simple, the ravioli lacked taste, and the lemon meringue was very plain and we ate so little of it that we received a complimentary milk ice cream which was nice (but also not very special).
The service was very good and the vibe of this place is great so it was a shame the food didnâ€™t quite leveled up.', 'rating': 3, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'Lihi Bavli', 'publishTime': '2023-07-15T14:45:52.217Z'}, {'text': 'As someone that travels really often and choose carefully where I eat, I have to say, I was dying for pasta and wanted something authentic and well balanced Z calabria and Kapara, were both on my list for a while, so when I finally got back to Tlv and had some time, I went. Have to say, they make the best pasta in Israel. From their carbonara to the Ox tail. The cacio e Pepe was ok. And Iâ€™ve had better. I was disappointed from the lack of wine in their selection (literally 3 really bad ones) and no cocktail menu (which is ok, I guess you go as authentic as it goes).
Biggest disappointment, was the fact that there are no mains. Literally, starters, salad and pasta.
Wish they had like a perfectly made fish or meat or something to balance the amount of carbs.
Anyway, amazing food. Skip the cacio e Pepe but defo make sure to order the Ox tail.
Iâ€™ll go again, next time, with my own wine.', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0L9MLvauCdTqMTUyYrLxfePQ2eF0YhqvWiBkroy-LgFXTCQI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'Dor', 'publishTime': '2023-05-22T08:35:36.977Z'}, {'text': "Probably the best carbonara I've had in the city.

{'rating': 4.4, 'placeId': 'ChIJ5QZ8ILBLHRUR8H3NBgx5ubA', 'reviews': [{'text': "So glad Mochikva finally opened up!
I've been dreaming about tapioca for a long time and my dream finally came true!!
Sarah makes an amazing hand made tapioca pearls and combines them in the most interesting and delicious drinks (my personal favorite is Taro)
In addition there are different kinds of mochi, traditional or ice cream, both are amazing!

{'rating': 4.8, 'placeId': 'ChIJg8icEyRLHRURV6HE8tMuwBo', 'reviews': [{'text': 'Pasta Aglio e olio had absolutely no flavor. Salad was just ok and carbonara arancini didnâ€™t taste like carbonara. Took a while to be seated, no host at entrance.', 'rating': 3, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXlKBajTlfQhYPuvHvpeXi3AnuVtp24LAW6oT1JOTEl8-VFEf82g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Romy Labi', 'publishTime': '2025-01-12T22:56:57.600Z'}, {'text': "Tasty food and lovely service. Pizza is very thin, haven't had that style in a while - was good. Ravioli portion is very generous. Semi-fredo dessert is amazing.", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUe9IIPyaxcJFe621OJ_P6HiawILK4zVVWzjk6rTWtZVJ9Iid9Klw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'authorName': 'Ofir Israel', 'publishTime': '2025-01-09T05:20:16.311Z'}, {'text': "Another great Italian restaurant by chef Bentzi Arbel, you really can't go wrong with any of the dishes.
The service was very friendly and kind.

I came for a casual lunch with a group of friends, and I ended up sharing with one of them, which was a great choice as we really had a hard time choosing out of the menu variety since everything sounded so delicious.

For starters we ordered the suppli carbonara that was served with a tomato sauce - the cheese inside was super stretchy as promised, and it was very creamy but surprisingly not too heavy as I expected it to be.

For mains we shared two of the pasta dishes.
The first was the asparagi fettuccine, which is a smooth sauce of pesto made out of asparagus & zucchini served with asparagus heads and topped with breadcrumbs. It was very delicious but a bit heavy in my opinion if we wouldn't have shared it.
The second pasta dish we tried was the vongole bianco fettuccine which was the prefect combination of lemony & creamy flavor (but not too heavy), served with clams, parsley and topped with breadcrumbs.

If you're looking for an authentic Italian experience, this could be the perfect choice.", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4SbXsD3O3jwXRJwecbpAbE8QA9ZmSj2peU_Fj8tr9l5cFQg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Maya Bar Ilan', 'publishTime': '2025-01-31T17:13:53.294Z'}, {'text': 'Delicious pastas, all very well made.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqqSdMlOdxq9k6X0VoxFha0r6zuy63I_vysAl32ClD2uxijA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Nadav Kra-Oz', 'publishTime': '2025-01-22T09:36:21.381Z'}, {'text': 'I love it', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIUQCiu3HESDQmJ-glUQCslpPzlY2KqGuXznfYl-cPxqFe1pQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Prisca s', 'publishTime': '2025-01-25T14:00:48.615Z'}, {'text': '××•×›×œ ××¢×•×œ×”, ×©×™×¨×•×ª ××¢×•×œ×”, ××•×•×™×¨×” ×˜×•×‘×”, ××—×™×¨×™× ×˜×•×‘×™×, ×§×™× ×•×— ×¡××™×¤×¨×“×• ××“×”×™×, ×§×•×§×˜×™×™×œ×™× ×˜×•×‘×™×. ×”×™×™×ª×™ ××•×•×ª×¨ ×¨×§ ×¢×œ ×”×¤×•×§××¦×³×” ×©×”×™×™×ª×” ××™×•×ª×¨×ª ×•×œ× ××¦×“×™×§×” 39 ×©×´×—. ×××œ×™×¥ ×‘×—×•× ×•× ×—×–×•×¨ ×©×•×‘ ×‘×•×•×“××•×ª', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'he', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxdvSynKjhIUtS3k7geKK_rvrf360Du6Kl3-xMzbROX-LlFg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': '×™×¨×“×Ÿ ××“×œ×©×˜×™×™×Ÿ', 'publishTime': '2025-01-26T11:23:00.131Z'}, {'text': '××•×›×œ ××¦×•×™×Ÿ ×•×œ× ××ª×—×›×, ××•×•×™×¨×” ×˜×•×‘×” ×•× ×¢×™××”.×‘×”×—×œ×˜ × ×—×–×•×¨ (× ×§×•×“×” ××—×ª ×œ×©×™×¤×•×¨ - ×¨×¦×™× ×• ×œ×”×–××™×Ÿ ×¢× ×”×§×™× ×•×— ×§×¤×” ×”×¤×•×š ×•× ×××¨ ×©×”× ×œ× ××—×–×™×§×™× ×—×œ×‘â€¦×—×‘×œ)', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'he', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwXEHFqeurOpFdDhOWBO3dEMBqyvpMIORjSPX6G2V7a1mF-gXv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'orly h', 'publishTime': '2025-02-05T19:29:07.947Z'}, {'text': '×”××•×›×œ ×”×™×” ×˜×¢×™× ×××•×“ ×•×’× ×”×™×™×Ÿ ×•×”×§×•×§×˜×™×™×œ×™×! We sat at the bar and enjoyed a perfect location.
The papaya salad is highly recommended and also the dish of the bannâ€™s (in my opinion the meat tastes good but the fish is better).  Nice selection of wine by glass menu.  Although there are better restaurants in Tel Aviv, in the "value for money" test the score of this place is perfect.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKUnVl1tvmZWqvQOFWfAbqL85PVb5gEqwmRi_4FG7q5Fs8bODCE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Yuval Degani', 'publishTime': '2022-08-11T22:07:36.237Z'}, {'text': 'One of my favorite spots in the Old North of Tel Aviv, this wine bar offers a truly enjoyable experience. What stands out initially is the rare combination of a quiet, relaxing atmosphere with a touch of nature, which is quite a rarity in the bustling city of Tel Aviv. The proximity to Yarkon Park only adds to the overall charm and ambiance.

The wine selection is diverse and reasonably priced, allowing wine enthusiasts to explore and taste a variety of options. Most of the dishes are designed for sharing, and I highly recommend taking advantage of this to sample as much as you can. Personally, I particularly enjoyed the Polenta, Corn stacks, and the artichoke salad.

The service provided at the wine bar was pleasant, with the staff offering helpful advice on food combinations. Moreover, the food was served promptly, allowing for a seamless dining experience.

This wine bar is an ideal setting for a date night or a gathering with friends. To add to the enjoyment, there is a happy hour until 19:30, making the experience even more delightful', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1NdNAAy5lx9I0LVg_Ru8zCMOvR2UWcsRsiVNKzPzi5w1exg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Itai Norman', 'publishTime': '2023-05-18T07:36:05.403Z'}, {'text': 'Really nice place, but no prices on wine bottle- gotta ask the waitress > didnâ€™t know > supervisors neither.

With a relatively small menu, they specialize in pasta with simple but accurate sauces that are clearly prepared and served with care. You canâ€™t reserve ahead of time, the place is popular so sometimes you might have to wait.
For me they lacked protein in their options but I enjoyed the dishes nevertheless. I donâ€™t recommend the burrata salad, it is mostly arugula. Also, they are quite expensive.', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWd86L58TgmF_nEVkeaAS0749VpHW3t6G5fiFmUm3O4fcCMXfIH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Dan H.', 'publishTime': '2023-04-04T18:05:31.811Z'}, {'text': 'Feels like Rome in the middle of Tel Aviv. Bentzi keeps the quality of the place and products, using fresh ingredients, serving amazing appetizers and pasta, and mouth-watering desserts. It was a pleasure.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9nkOK9l-wn4EXGyBUDSql_NC_FV3ql5RxM8_D_9DDo55S_oI1Ng=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'authorName': 'rachel kogan', 'publishTime': '2022-04-25T11:23:59.944Z'}, {'text': 'Delicious pasta and salad - salad had a bit too much olive oil but it was still delicious. We got a bottle of wine and the wine was great. Would def come back and try a different pasta :)', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVw3ebSN5xu0MaEFCyFnzxCjyaB_MKKyt3tNb1C8w6Q3tONHRvV0g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Dalya Forman', 'publishTime': '2023-05-23T18:03:32.773Z'}, {'text': "The good:
Food is hot, tastes fresh and despite the portions not looking so big, they are filling.

The bad:
Seating area is outdoor only, and it's all smoking. If you hate smoking, DO NOT GO HERE. Someone is bound to light up a cigarette or joint, and it really ruins the whole experience.

Wait times can be very very long. You have to scan a QR code at the entrance to get onto the waiting list. We had 15 guests ahead of us, which took 50 minutes. And while there are benches in front of the restaurant, it's directly underneath a tree with pooping bats. Not great :)

Lastly, the food is a bit overpriced. Starters are 50-60 shekels and pasta is 70-80 shekels.", 'rating': 2, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdEPUBWI3LwjEumWhC8u5wZJgfPRrF1eD10BkYRozVIEE7Je1aXA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Asaf Sagi', 'publishTime': '2022-10-18T20:15:26.470Z'}, {'text': 'Restaurant Review: "Kapara" - A Taste of Authentic Italian Cuisine

As a lover of Italian food, I am always on the lookout for new places to try and assess based on my personal benchmark dish, Carbonara. I must say, "Kapara" in Tel Aviv has undoubtedly served me the best Carbonara I have found in Israel so far, and I've had the opportunity to sample quite a few. When judging an Italian restaurant, I always consider how closely they can replicate the original flavors I experienced in Italy, and "Kapara" has truly nailed it!

To begin with, the spaghetti was cooked to perfection, al dente just as it should be. What surprised me the most was that I didn't need to add anything to enhance the dish. No salt, no parmesan, no pepperâ€”everything was already perfectly balanced. "Kapara" respects the traditional ingredients and doesn't stray by adding unnecessary elements such as cream or beans. The Carbonara here is simple, yet it packs a powerful punch of flavors.

My dining companion had the Amatriciana, and the sauce was executed with great precision. It had the same boldness and intensity as the Carbonara, yet it didn't overpower the dish. The flavors were rich and delightful.

For dessert, we indulged in a beautiful Torta Ricotta. It was not overly sweet, which suited my taste perfectly. As a pleasant surprise, we were also treated to a complementary Tiramisu, which was enjoyable, but I must admit that I preferred the Torta Ricotta.

If I were to make one remark, it would be regarding the portion size. It could be just a bit bigger. I wouldn't mind paying a little extra to ensure a more substantial serving. After all, it is a restaurant, and while I understand that prices have increased and everything is becoming more expensive, it would be nice to have a slightly larger portion.

The ambiance at "Kapara" is lovely, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. The restaurant is situated in a trendy location, adding to its appeal.

I will undoubtedly return to "Kapara" to savor their delightful Carbonara once again. If you're seeking an authentic Italian culinary experience, I highly recommend this restaurant.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnh_FrGRaY0hSGsdRqnFOm9Rk-yY34aAgz1TXpBRghvdIUCVA6sg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Itzik Ben Yehuda', 'publishTime': '2023-07-09T19:27:20.614Z'}, {'text': "××– ×©××¢×ª×™ ×œ× ××¢×˜ ×¢×œ ×”××§×•× ×•×’× ×”×ª××•× ×•×ª ×‘××™× ×¡×˜×’×¨× × ×¨××• ××’×¨×•×ª :) ×”××•×›×œ ×”×™×” ×××© ×˜×¢×™×, ×”××•×•×™×¨×” ×‘××§×•× × ×—××“×”, ×”××œ×¦×¨ ×”××œ×™×¥ ×œ× ×• ×¢×œ ×¤×¡×˜×” ××œ×” ×¨×•×× ×” ×©×”×™×™×ª×” ××“×”×™××” (×¨×•×˜×‘ ×¢×’×‘× ×™×•×ª, ×—×ª×™×›×•×ª ×¦'×× ×§×™×•×ª ×‘×©×¨× ×™×•×ª ×©×œ ×—×¦×™×œ×™×, ×’×‘×™× ×ª ×¨×™×§×•×˜×”), ×—×‘×¨×” × ×•×¡×¤×ª ××›×œ×” ××ª ×”×¤×¡×˜×” ×”×œ×™××•× ×™×ª ×©×”×™×™×ª×” ×’× ×˜×¢×™××” ××‘×œ ××™×Ÿ ×¢×œ ×©×™×œ×•×‘ ×©×œ ×¢×’×‘× ×™×•×ª ×—×¦×™×œ ×•×¨×™×§×•×˜×” ğŸ˜‹, ×œ×§×™× ×•×— ×”×–×× ×• ×˜×¨××™×¡×• (×©×™× ×• ××ª ×¦×•×¨×ª ×”×”×’×©×”, ×–×” ××’×™×¢ ×›×—×ª×™×›×” ×›××• ×‘×›×œ ××§×•× ×•×œ× ×—×ª×™×›×” ×©×©××™× ×œ×š ×¢× ×›×£ ×”×’×©×”), ×”×§×™× ×•×— ×”×™ ×˜×¢×™× ×•××¡×¤×¨×¡×•××™ ××š ×œ× ××ª×•×§ ××“×™, ×××œ×™×¦×” ×××•×“ ×¢×œ ×”××¡×¢×“×” ××—×–×•×¨ ×©×•×‘ â˜ºï¸ğŸ", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'he', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAOs8gOmiOJZ__6cTgDejfpCgAnQ2WDuq1Q3OnVCDWUSZ_SQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': '×¨×—×œ ×¤×—× ×¡', 'publishTime': '2025-02-02T23:49:18.157Z'}, {'text': '××—×ª ×”××™×˜×œ×§×™×•×ª ×”×™×•×ª×¨ ×˜×¢×™××•×ª ×©×”×™×™×ª×™ ×‘×”×Ÿ. ×”×œ×›× ×• ×¢× ×”××œ×¦×ª ×”××œ×¦×¨, ×•××›×œ× ×• ×× ×•×ª ××¢×•×œ×•×ª!! {'rating': 4.4, 'placeId': 'ChIJMUlwH9lLHRURKGXMwD-f3Bs', 'reviews': [{'text': "It was quite a first experience and I was impressed by such an enterprising guy at the cashier who gave us a glass of draught beer on the house!
The automated ordering at the kiosk with pictures was fun and easy and makes so much sense with Thai food!
The yam pla was delicious, so was the satay. The jungle curry with pork I was disappointed  wasn't hot enough but the pork was very tender! All ingredients were super fresh the place was super clean and I'd love to go back", 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVf_ywfHWaJpTD2nRL-dxdU-0aN37FBNqI5oCIawZa1zRjMRrRYOA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Nat', 'publishTime': '2022-08-23T06:04:35.549Z'}, {'text': 'After reading countless good reviews and the restaurant is always full of diners to the brim I finally decided to visit the restaurant myself for the first time.  The dishes are very tasty and the raw ingredients are fresh and the atmosphere is fantastic.  I also liked the self-service concept because I donâ€™t like waiters service.  Order through a touch screen and once ready then you are served a tray with the order packed in disposable utensils but in plastic packages which I did not like because I advocate a green environment.  The biggest minus of all this, is the price! The best thing in this place is the Music! mainly Britpop and Rock and not what you expect , there was a very unique playlist. The only issue I had is that the music was too loud and it made it hard for us to talk. In conclusion, Shay Braha, I am truly grateful to have had the pleasure of dining here and experiencing the epitome of culinary excellence under your guidance. {'rating': 4.1, 'placeId': 'ChIJ0f4b7olLHRURtMCNs1_NKnQ', 'reviews': [{'text': 'One of my favorite cafes in Tel Aviv. Breakfast is one of the best too find in town and so consistent. One of the best coffees that can be found. Desserts are a hit or miss but the food is excellent!', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX29Igbf-4CAt92ok7TOK6SQ0V_dmwN6D0K3kaoFctbf3c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Dani Levin', 'publishTime': '2023-03-02T21:00:03.000Z'}, {'text': "What a great place in the heart of Tel-Aviv!!
You can sit outside and do some people watching, or inside to escape the heat, or in the back patio if you want to smoke after your meal.
Great and friendly staff, that was quick and not pushy.
The bagels looked so good, so I had to try it and ordered a roast beef bagel. Slices of beef, slaw and a spicy mustard, on a bagel. Great sandwich! Could use some more beef, but the flavor combo, which is not new, was done correctly and it was delicious. Also had a Nola breakfast. Two eggs, salad, hash browns, cream cheese, avocado, and a bagel. The portion was generous and everything was good. Except for the hash brown. It was probably made in a large batch and than they cut and reheat the portion on a griddle. At least that's how it tastes. It was too dense and didn't have those classic pointy potato ends that crisp up when you fry it.
I also got a Nola cocktail, with OJ, whiskey and honey. It was pretty good. Definitely a nice change from the classic mimosa or bloody Mary for breakfast.
All in all, I would definitely come back here for brunch, or lunch, or anytime of the day.", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrOhpfQ_7-6dGULPjFKEFZPDMxycOPrgsgdVlDMJPx0w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'Gadi Yekutiel', 'publishTime': '2023-06-11T14:08:42.000Z'}, {'text': "Ot was overall alright. Cant wait to come back again', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjf2okt-Txz6y-n0w3R5E3b5y8UBbty6uNPC8mxEIF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Mia Posner', 'publishTime': '2023-10-03T17:58:52.000Z'}, {'text': "Will not go back.

Food was OK, though pricy.
Menu was not clear. We thought we were ordering a Tuna dish (named red sashimi) which turned out to be watermelon, which is something the staff should have explained.
Wine was ridiculously expensive, even for Tel Aviv.

We sat on the bar which we normally do and love, but the service was really bad. The staff was not coordinated, they served us the wrong drinks and cleared food we asked not to clear.
Staff poured sauce on my friend and barely apologised.

Adding a response to the place's comment below -
We asked for a glass of white wine and got a 74!!! shekel glass. There was no Wine menu to look at...

As for the price of the food -
1. I don't know where your averages are from, but if they include every expensive restaurant in TLV of course you will make yourself look cheap. let me compare to other places (that I think you can agree are high end), this was totally on the same price scale. SunYoung - 55 shekels, Ouzeria (which is expensive) 70 shekels, Dok - 70.
2. life is about value for money, not just price. We felt we paid a lot for what we got.
3. The main issue with the watermelon sashimi was that we didn't know we were ordering watermelon, as you can see by my original comment. The food and coffee are excellent, and everything is of the highest quality. However, the prices are quite high ,especially those of the drinks(27 shekels for matcha!!). Great vegan options, sweet and savoury. On weekends it tends to be very crowded and the wait might last a long time, which isn't so fun on sunny or rainy days. So I recommend visiting on weekdays when the traffic is much lighter.  The service varies between excellent and poor, depends on the waiter. Got the GDB combo. The burger was very good. Could use a little more salt in the meat, and maybe a few seconds less on the grill, but still a great burger. The toppings really go together and add a lot of different flavors. The fries are fresh and the portion is generous.

If you donâ€™t mind that there is a lot going on definitely visit the place, if you mind it - order to take away - worth it!

Delicious burgers ğŸ” !', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUty1mNlqOMOrn3OBp3KqZINxHWkT-85ozyQr5lHiZ2HISCvMQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Jagoda Posluszna', 'publishTime': '2023-06-18T14:38:41.351Z'}, {'text': "I must express my utmost admiration for the culinary delights I had the pleasure of experiencing at this esteemed establishment. The gastronomic journey commenced with the black bun, an extraordinary masterpiece that delighted my senses and left an indelible impression. Every morsel was savored with unparalleled delight, so much so that I was compelled to savor even the leftover crumbs, for no fragment of this exquisite creation could be left unappreciated.

The internal workings of their kitchen were nothing short of extraordinary. As an avid epicurean, I reveled in the opportunity to witness the culinary artistry unfold before my very eyes. The precision and finesse with which the culinary team orchestrated their movements in perfect harmony was truly a sight to behold. The cleanliness and meticulousness with which they operated further enhanced the dining experience, elevating it to unprecedented heights.

Regrettably, I must convey a minor grievance. The external ambiance, though pleasant, did not exude the same level of perfection as the culinary prowess within. While the establishment's attention to detail was evident in the kitchen, it appeared that the same level of meticulousness did not extend to the exterior surroundings. This small disparity detracted from the overall ambiance and, regrettably, influenced my rating.

Furthermore, it is worth noting that the prices were on the higher end of the spectrum. While the quality of the cuisine justified the cost to a certain extent, the pricing structure may prove a deterrent to those seeking more budget-friendly options.

Lastly, it is important to mention that the establishment operates on a self-service basis. While this does not detract from the culinary excellence, it is a factor to consider for those seeking a more traditional, full-service dining experience.

In conclusion, this establishment has undoubtedly left an indelible mark on my gastronomic journey. The exceptional quality of the burgers, the invisible symphony in their kitchen, and the meticulous attention to detail warrant commendation. While minor shortcomings in the external ambiance and pricing structure were observed, they do not overshadow the overall excellence. Lamb Bacon and Cheddar is superb. The crispness perfectly complements the savory filling.  (Softer crepes, on the other hand, go well with sweet ones such as banana Nutella.)

The sizzled lamb bacon is also impeccable. I was already enjoying the aroma while waiting and am not disappointed. As part of the crepe, the lamb bacon is neither overpoweringly brittle due to overcooking nor too greasy due to undercooking.

And the hearty gooey, melty cheese! Pulling the cheese with each bite just make me soooooo happy. If only I am audacious enough to take a selfie of me stretching the cheese with my teeth.

Totally recommend it.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbrxi3utsiaETwX_HN6B3qZknl4l5Fnz98v7NDlEDN39HHnD_9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'X', 'publishTime': '2022-09-01T18:19:12.837Z'}, {'text': "Place is nice with great atmosphere. They also have great pizzas.', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDcjzv1anXPhecKSm06ZILlp7KUEZJLi1QYPT6LXr6ig=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Saba Golbandi', 'publishTime': '2023-02-04T23:23:04.000Z'}, {'text': "Nice place for having a beer, and most importantly one of the best Pizzas in town. The place was supposed to stay open till 3.00am. However, one hour later we got told that the bar was closing and I was not able to get anymore drinks, even though I had already paid for them. Moreover, the managing personnel was really rude to me, playing me as a fool when I tried to make them notice about the fact that I had came just one hour before and hadnâ€™t served that much to drink. Therefore I would not recommend anybody to go there. I didnâ€™t appreciate at all my time there.', 'rating': 1, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIwqAb32IcGvCFcZWFX9Y6n1zpayvPFLyaf-w_5QiWc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'ludovico fumagalli', 'publishTime': '2023-01-17T00:37:46.000Z'}, {'text': "I love this bar but it has its issues.

The happy hour is the way to go as the food and alcohol are extremely cheap, and the tracks are worth it only if you're planning to drink A LOT. So I recommend visiting during the happy hours.

The pizzas are a big plus. delicious and extremely worth it during the happy hour as they cost 60 shekels for their best ones.

But my main problems with this bar are the uncomfortable seating areas and the fact that the service is a bit slow.
The waiters are nice but when the place is crammed it's really hard to get their attention.

And for the seating, I recommend you book a place inside the bar, as outside will be uncomfortable for large groups.

All in all, I would recommend it because of the cheap alcohol and great food during happy hours.", 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeGONLlL9DommVV1K-wpvy4AOICKFf9f9OTbwdinpahDw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'eyal kapon', 'publishTime': '2022-10-07T15:01:22.000Z'}, {'text': 'Reasonable service, no heating outside. {'rating': 4.3, 'placeId': 'ChIJsa4ffHhMHRURAyYnPiQ5nSY', 'reviews': [{'text': 'A nice Pizza place which also serves as a bar (well, the place is also called "pizza and bar" so, makes sense ğŸ˜†).

Surprisingly, it was the only place around that area, that was open during "Chol Hamoed Pessach", and was selling bread!
I assume they are also open during Saturday.

Pizza is nice, unpretentious and decently priced for a quarter of a tray (2 slices): 19 for plane margarita, 22 for toppings and 25 for special/meat toppings. If you are super hungry 1 quarter won't be enough probably but for a light hunger it's perfect.

I was there around noon and it was self service, meaning you order and get the pizza at the counter. The ğŸ•man was nice and even gave us a free slice because the one we got wasn't really a perfect quarter.

The tables were clean and everything was very inviting, including the music.

The only reason I'm giving it a 4star review is the toilet upstairs: the smell from one of the stalls was unbearable and I had to leave the door open for air, so I won't die from the stench...
Also there was no paper to dry your hands so... the upstairs area needs some work and then the place will be a 5 star place!

Enjoy ğŸ‰', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXU4Bvkl9qcMdOuZBWgWnzcOGsEpI2srLj-Oz8h8NshxbY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'authorName': 'Ori Goshen', 'publishTime': '2022-04-26T06:09:51.000Z'}, {'text': 'Super tasty pizza love the sweet potato slices', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfULkEZpFSj7Cc_dRQFFOyv2mvEOrYEDSxUqkVFwDJr9s-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'AlinkaM', 'publishTime': '2022-05-22T10:53:34.000Z'}, {'text': 'I like thin pizza and in this place they make it very tasty with great toppings. We ordered vegan breakfast for too which included lots of things in it and looked super promising. Food was okay, coffee was way below average ğŸ˜” they brought us orange juice ğŸ§ƒ that was not a fresh juice as was said in menu, but waiter was nice enough to change it for carrot as thatâ€™s the only juice they squeeze freshly in here (would be nice if he would say it in advance). At the end it was written in Hebrew description of breakfast â€œkonfitoriat tutâ€, that was missing in English version of menu, when we asked for it we got bread and Nutella..in vegan breakfast.. I mean, not a big deal but small things like that make big difference in an overall impression from a place
Atmosphere was rather cold and music on a second floor sounds just like a noise coz of a speaker, maybe itâ€™s nicer to sit outside but not on a hot summer day like now.', 'rating': 3, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYHh_a9Q7t7k9990YpdcGjVutprxqPrArDIqxSBcdWWQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Aleksandra K', 'publishTime': '2023-08-12T09:03:48.000Z'}, {'text': 'I had the most lovely meal here! Highly recommend this restaurant for a truly authentic â€œIsraeliâ€ experience, start to finish!', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6r8wSLxQ14OFHkmtjgrXMw_ZPM4hczrix79LEpaAa=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Katherine Kurlon', 'publishTime': '2023-07-27T13:21:32.000Z'}, {'text': 'Nice breakfast and a cosy place to sit outside. We visit the cafe twice in our short vocation and had the breakfast for two for 145 shekel. It includes coffee and juice which is a good deal. The other day we had shakshuka which was also delicious.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIM9TCQkXsuiKMB4sxBRYPZdXwslScHUR4C0tUtUKggcEM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'K. U.', 'publishTime': '2023-02-25T14:40:42.000Z'}, {'text': 'Go for the Shakshuka and stay for the warm cookie with ice cream.
Our daughter had the avo toast and then ordered a second.  She said it was the best she has ever had.
The service was great, the place is charming but the brunch is AMAZING.
It made me want to live in the neighborhood so this could be our place for Sunday brunch.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcR0BAljag4gv5W41Hg4Fo7Z4erUYXwKTrGZiGWtZCdqI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Ruchika', 'publishTime': '2023-01-15T17:45:01.000Z'}, {'text': 'We wanted to have a real Tel-Aviv experience, but it wasn't pleasant!!
We ordered a breakfast for two 135 ILS (plate of food, 2 portions of eggs+ bread, 4 drinks).

There was hair in my son's omelette. He almost vomited, it was disgusting.
We told the waitress and she said "I'm so sorry we'll bring a new one". She brought a new one, my son felt ok, so he ate the omelette.
We ordered 3 lattes+ orange juice that are included.
1. Usually if you made a big mistake like A HAIR IN THE FOOD, at least you ask if guests want something like desert or something to cheer them. No one asked us!
2. The waitress brought a check with 4 drinks for which she wanted us to pay!! But they are included already. She said: oh, sorry, someone thought that you've ordered a bigger portion, I will fix it. So in the end the total price was supposed to be 135 ILS
3. Before I gave her my card she asked : "do you want to give us a tip"?
I didn't want to. But, I said 10%, because of the hair. I think that's also too much.

If not these bit pleasant situations, it could be a nice place.
It's crowded, tables are small, you sit close to other people (nothing new).
But, honestly nothing special.
The line was about 10-15 minutes before we could sit .', 'rating': 1, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgwpq2RPHK2JYBaIukS44kYhV3vpD0I4nnwBVNGyJQlQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Elena Shorokhova', 'publishTime': '2023-01-03T21:37:59.000Z'}, {'text': '××•×›×œ ×˜×¢×™× ×‘××—×™×¨×™× ×¡×‘×™×¨×™× ×•××•×•×™×¨×” × ×¢×™××”.

The stuff was great and kind.

About the atmosphere - if you suffer from cigarettes, then you should think twice before coming here", 'rating': 3, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3WKfO1ppxUKcRf9SGskCYjmCVupHcInyTccHYnTW6Ot1S9MCfqw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Tza Leh', 'publishTime': '2025-01-18T17:09:30.818Z'}, {'text': 'Nice place, we went on Friday noon, wasnâ€™t crowded at all, we set outside in the yard, it was great atmosphere.
The food was nice, nothing special, but good.
The service was very slow for a kinda not full restaurant, there was 1+1 on the cocktails which was great.', 'rating': 3, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJao32qPpIYRVsyoDZ8OaYoW5EvBa1aH10NyyYncK8FyrWzKYwAA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Michal Ben Netanel', 'publishTime': '2025-01-18T19:43:18.546Z'}, {'text': 'A cute new wine bar.
We chose to seat inside on the bar, as outside it was too humid.
The inside space is small but cozy, the bar only had 5 seats.
The wine list was very interesting, and we chose what the bartender recommended.
We took bread (which was amazing), great ceviche, and two salads. Personally we found the tomato salad just okay as it had too many spices and zaatar.
Overall a very nice and quiet location.', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'Lihi Bavli', 'publishTime': '2023-07-22T15:05:48.773Z'}, {'text': "One of my new favorite spots in Tel Aviv, this place has an amazing location. Despite being close to the busy Dizingoff Street, it offers a surprisingly peaceful atmosphere.

The wine selection here is quite extensive, featuring a variety of reds, whites, roses, and even orange wines (yes, you read that right!). The restaurant is cleverly designed with different areas, providing comfortable seating options for all kinds of gatherings, from couples enjoying a glass of wine to groups of friends dining together.

I thoroughly enjoyed every dish I tried, as they were all outstanding, with unique flavors and refreshing twists on local ingredients. My personal favorites include the tomato salad, sea fish fillet, and Parisian gnocchi.

The service was also fantastic, adding to the overall positive experience.

{'rating': 4.8, 'placeId': 'ChIJwRsgu5pNHRURMDw2d7hxb4g', 'reviews': [{'text': "The Best Crispy Chicken in Town!
If you're looking for the ultimate crispy chicken burger, this is the place to go! The chicken is perfectly seasoned, juicy on the inside, and delightfully crispy on the outside. Every bite feels like a celebration of flavor.

The service is just as amazing as the food. The staff is incredibly friendly and welcoming, making you feel right at home from the moment you walk in. The warm atmosphere adds to the overall experience, whether you're dining alone, with friends, or with family.

I highly recommend this spot for anyone who loves great food and even better service. It's a must-visit for burger lovers!", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8jN4Mhg6_q0ck3ZoaLPPo8-8nIUnQ_gfElWQfA0cB8ydSlSMxPQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Ruby Journo', 'publishTime': '2024-11-17T19:45:28.381Z'}, {'text': 'Very nice people, but the food was not good:

{'rating': 4.4, 'placeId': 'ChIJ0xIHtoJMHRUR2bYUc7-ZZl0', 'reviews': [{'text': 'I am a repeat customer. I come back because the food has been consistent and always exceeds my expectations.  Today I ordered the chicken burger and fries and the burger was crispy and had two generous pieces. Fries are fresh and I always get the chipotle sauce on the side. I would place the burgers as a serious contender for one of the better burger places in Tel-Aviv. There is seating inside and also outside but it is on a busy road. The music is good but I always think that the music is always too loud in most places. Overall I like the burgers and the place. Small details also make a difference,  they have wet wipes and an ample supply of napkins, it makes a difference.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4MNICeDqCyFsVAqdA9As1SGh4mJEpmAknLQ1JTGGkNzKMLQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Brad Hofman', 'publishTime': '2022-11-04T18:14:22.880Z'}, {'text': 'As two American girls we LOVED this restaurant. {'rating': 5, 'placeId': 'ChIJAdPLw7hMHRURA_kiNcaFpk4', 'reviews': [{'text': "I travelled all the from Ireland to get inked by these guys and the result was more incredible than I could have imagined. The detail and precision is unreal. amazing detailed work, so good I'm travelling back to for another round :).
The studio is really chilled out and relaxed, everyone's really friendly, service is great, it made the whole experience one to remember.
thanks a million!!", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEMIPnRTvD7GKWqYf4lMIpahTe7B3OTOkzUjgHhgEB=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Zen Donegan', 'publishTime': '2023-03-31T12:10:34.000Z'}, {'text': 'I traveled to Tel Aviv from Alabama to visit my brother and his family. {'rating': 4.5, 'placeId': 'ChIJdQJ2939LHRURZmSMcBu4tfo', 'reviews': [{'text': 'The restaurant offers a variety of Mediterranean inspired food and drinks, with some interesting adaptation to the Israeli taste. Was there for dinner. Salads (we had Greek salad an Caesar salad) have very tasty ingredients and vegetables and are nicely served. Then we accompanied with a tasty Orange pizza (no fruit in the ingredients, name comes from the colours of the topping), which comes with a crispy base, mozzarella and goat cheeses and fresh leek (a bit too dry on top for my taste). A Sangria drink (please do not expect the traditional Spanish version ğŸ˜‹, but more a revisited Spritz wish berries) was a perfect and fresh support. The place is pretty peculiar, since tables are positioned on some large wood stages in front of the restaurant, that is just on King George street. Recommended for a non traditional Israeli dinner.', 'rating': 4, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWg02Dvg_ppGSe8gz2jhQdc_8-i3knMCsbhP0WpKKlnC8M=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Stefano P', 'publishTime': '2023-05-28T04:07:46.000Z'}, {'text': 'Cool place, great food! {'rating': 4.2, 'placeId': 'ChIJ4SoclmJLHRURHArSXtGHgjo', 'reviews': [{'text': 'Delicious sushi in a comfortable and friendly setting. The staff was welcoming and even handed out complimentary shots of sake. I had a hard time deciding what to order; the waitress was patient and helpful while I made my decision.
I ended up getting the black Tokyo roll which was super-tasty! Iâ€™d highly suggest it to those who love avocadoâ€” thereâ€™s avocado both inside and outside the roll. The tuna in the roll tasted fresh and yummy!
I recommend this spot if youâ€™re looking for some nice sushi in a pleasant environment!', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK05jPe2ExRYK73tLkYKPzyBOCWe2z-Q0fd8Sevvz8BPS6qrw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Mayan R', 'publishTime': '2024-07-23T12:13:49.000Z'}, {'text': 'Fantastic dining experience. Travelling from Australia to Tel-Aviv and found this amazing gem in the heart of the city. Amazing food, incredible service and great vibes! Highly recommend.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmboZspm9AlT1e7YET2kEW3ZNMoy7UfJMPL-lLOZ32pNjeNxk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Dion Gory', 'publishTime': '2024-08-09T21:20:15.000Z'}, {'text': 'One of my favourite places to eat lately. Great food for an affordable price. I regularly eat in as well as order from Wolt. Very quick and efficient service.

Amazing soup options. I got addicted to their Miso soup. It is SO GOOD. I order it 3 times a week. A big portion of soup with a lot of tofu inside. Sushi were also pretty good, I would recommend their specialties - my favourite is the ones covered in avocado and salmon. All super fresh ingredients.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXG4TwuDMP1JtCNcJ2Mj_TGPANaoLorac7uFTUhqD5rD-iZNg4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Mary Grant', 'publishTime': '2023-09-16T18:09:52.000Z'}, {'text': "This place is a joke. I came from far away to discover that they close the Kitchen at random hours. 1.5 hr before closing. Mind you it's a sushi Restaurant not a bar!!! This is the second time. If you want to get some food there you need to arrive at noon and don't believe their opening hours. It's a lie!", 'rating': 1, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2Bo9ndzi1XSpzd6r2qw4HjbMGyg7pxx62dIJ4tGwyIxGP8Sod=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'authorName': 'Gaul Top', 'publishTime': '2024-07-31T19:46:23.000Z'}, {'text': 'Becarefull, they have 2 menu. One for tourist (in english with lower prices / old prices) and one in Hebrew (higher prices / new prices). When we ordered take away, the waitress "forgot" to tell us that the prices are different and charged us the prices in the hebrew menu. Once the last one of us was about to pay, he noticed that the total was more expensive that what he calculated. After showing it to the waitress, and her to check with the manager, she came back and said the english menu is not up to date and the prices are the one in the hebrew menu. We didnt agreed since most of us paid and because it is false advertisement. The owner came, and put straight and strongly that the prices are the one in the hebrew menu and not one in the english menu. Then the situation escalated quickly between us and the owner of the place. She barely said "sorry our mistake, here a refund or here a small gift as compensation". She standed her point and just let the last of us who didnt paid yet to pay the old price. That's all.
Just for you to know dear owner, I would had choose something different if I knew that my chirashi would cost me 79 instead of 74 (which is already expensive).
Some peoples would say yes it's only 5 shekel. But my 5 shekel plus what my friends paid more, we could had get an additional dish.
Even more, how many peoples didnt take a look to their ticket and just paid the "new prices" instead of the "old ones"?
If you were an honest owner, you would at least had put a sticker on the english menu saying the prices are not up to date and need to take a look on the hebrew one. Or take those menu out of your restaurant. Or just agree with us with simple apology. Your behavior is a big stain on your restaurant where for us it was nice to come time to time.

Customer service: -10/10
Waitress : 10/10 (nice, smiling and helping)
Owner:-10/10

Offers a verity of vegetarian and vegan options. We really enjoyed the wild rice avocado salad with its fresh yogurt dip and also took the breakfast platter. We liked it so much we came back a fee weeks later and took the same dishes :)
I also really liked the cold chai latte with almond milk.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'authorName': 'Lihi Bavli', 'publishTime': '2024-08-11T06:09:14.898Z'}, {'text': 'We were a diverse group of vegans, vegetarians and meat eaters and everyone found something delicious to eat. I warmly recommend this restaurant with delicious fresh local food and a charming wait staff', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjKeeQLikUqtt90yQQZ__IpSDkgCeSOfcFKcR-tDjZz6f0YIVw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Eva Rockman', 'publishTime': '2024-12-03T10:07:56.060Z'}, {'text': "Good vibes, fun techno music, light breeze and relaxing atmosphere, accompanied by fresh and tasty food.
I eat gluten free and sugar free, so in most places I have a hard time finding what to order. Here I could basically choose almost any item on the menu!
Everything looks great, most options are either vegan, vegetarian or gluten free and the meat is eco friendly.
My partner had the Meat Shakshuka, I had the Musaka and together we ordered the Sabich opening dish. We could have done without the latter, but it was super delicious! Both main courses were excellent, nicely presented and we were so hungry that I forgot to take pictures. Trust me, though, it's awesome. There's a buckwheat pita for gluten free dishes and it's wonderful.
The self service order only takes a few seconds and the food is served by waiters with a most welcoming manner.
Prices are fair and the staff are friendly and helpful. It was a great pleasure and I had the best time. Thank you! :)", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGP9QAUg82bXQuV36ubGL5y-xP4lr4VieVOzvzdPJqyJ9fj9ni3g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'authorName': 'Eti Or', 'publishTime': '2020-06-19T13:49:37.578Z'}, {'text': '×”×–×× ×ª×™ ×©× ×™×¦×œ ×¦×¨×•×‘ ×”×’×™×¢ ×›××• ×©× ×™×¦×œ ××˜×•×’×Ÿ ×§×¨ ×©×¢×•×¢×™×ª ×—×©×‘×ª×™ ×™×¨×•×§×” ×”×’×™×¢ ×§×˜× ×™×•×ª.×‘×™×§×ª×™ ×œ×—×× ×”×’×™×¢ ×—×¨×•×š ×œ× ×˜×¢×™× ×•×”××•×¨×– ×‘×¨ ×”×ª×™×™×‘×© ×›× ×¨××” ×—×™×× ×”×›×•×œ ×™×—×“.×‘×™×§×©×ª×™ ×œ×”×—×œ×™×£ ×œ××•×¨×– ×œ×‘×Ÿ ×”×’×™×¢ ×’× ×™×‘×© ×××›×–×‘ ×××•×“.×”×©××¨×ª×™ ××ª ×”×›×•×œ ×¨×§ ×©× ×™×¦×œ ××›×œ×ª×™ ×œ×œ× ×”×¦×™×¤×•×™ ×©×™×œ××ª×™ ×œ×œ× ×˜×™×¤ ×××›×–×‘', 'rating': 2, 'language': 'he', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1TQCgpISAfG6vK9TyNqKNY1RnskuHESFJcOK-A9-sMEminvpk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Menashe Somech', 'publishTime': '2024-12-03T19:23:43.850Z'}, {'text': '**×¢×“×›×•×Ÿ 10.12**

I got a yummy iced coffee with almond milk and a piece of their famous carrot cake which was divine and indeed worth the hype. The prices are very convenient, which was a nice surprise since I expected the food to be way more expensive due to its great quality and it being freshly made.
The service was amazing, the guy who took my order was super nice and had a very cheerful and happy vibe.
The seating area is peaceful and quite with great music selection. Great for a chat hangout with a friend or even for studying.
Very recommended! external_data: {'rating': 4.4, 'placeId': 'ChIJF7NQo4NMHRURpaQHvxj2Afs', 'reviews': [{'text': 'The place lost the taste and the charm. I arrived at 3pm and ordered pita and fries. The fries are raw inside and burned on the outside and taste like burnt oil,  the meat is like rubber and tasteless dry! the whole pita was dry like an unbuttered toast from stale bread. The team did not care as it was shift change hour or something. They simply started collecting sauce bottles from the tables while customers including me were still eating. Another one was sweeping the floor and hair and dust were all in the air shining under the afternoon sun midair over the prep counter. There were no pickles and no one cared.\n\nThe worst is exactly this,  the staff did not care! Shame, it used to be a great place when opened.', 'rating': 2, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVN-CYIY52AvmSdDQuMD-BD4hnvdihhRqXay6ut6I_8gqAG9ac=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'kauina k', 'publishTime': '2025-02-26T13:56:12.105Z'}], 'priceLevel': 'PRICE_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED', 'dogFriendly': False, 'openingHours': {'friday': '11:00-16:00', 'monday': '11:00-23:00', 'sunday': '11:00-23:00', 'tuesday': '11:00-23:00', 'saturday': '17:00-23:00', 'thursday': '11:00-00:00', 'wednesday': '11:00-23:00'}}

We will definitely come again!', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXB5KCdyaA8HZFg8pkyOEwjKSFjnuhaQow5qWxLBrd18Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'authorName': 'Michal Elia Kamal', 'publishTime': '2022-12-25T07:51:47.000Z'}, {'text': 'The street block was out of electricity when we went but they had a buffet style salad bar open regardless. Lots of delicious fresh salads just perfect for a hot summer day.
The service was super warm and friendly, they even tried to reduce the price on our orders.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoIoFDFmDRb2X1_CjLd2IDlO8p_BpkZZ5mN85OvdZU81X7=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Di Lu', 'publishTime': '2023-07-28T15:52:50.000Z'}, {'text': "This is a genuine culinary treat of a restaurant. Yes it has typical expected vegan dishes, but also some real different options. Our family isn't vegan but we will often eat vegetarian. We were not in any way disappointed. Beautiful food, real flavour, excellent quality and presentation. Highlights were the lentil meatballs, the vegan egg (amazing) and the sloppy burger. The restaurant provided lovely bread and hummus as a free entrÃ©e and also cakes/sweets at the end.
Do not miss out on this experience. The owner is rightly proud of his restaurant, very friendly.", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9LS-kS8Ej3HO80wMAXOl6R-6W3SaxaCoMEMIoZ-5lGRc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Matty S 146', 'publishTime': '2023-08-12T23:12:07.000Z'}, {'text': 'We ate the arais and the classic burger. They were both excellent, very recommended. The staff was kind and generous.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmW5dMtFLIskORHLAmmgcDGz2Rdw_SZvRWwRmbpKEQP0a3=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'authorName': 'Juli Hanono', 'publishTime': '2023-09-24T11:08:16.000Z'}, {'text': 'I love this place!
I feel like it still has a way to go before I can give it a 5 stars review, but nonetheless it's still really nice, the food is good, the service is good, and the prices are good!
What's not to like?
Now you might be asking - "So why just 4 stars?". Answer is - the food is good but can definitely be taken to the next level, the service is good when it's available but I would suggest to hire just one more person to really be available to all customers all the time, and the atmosphere can also get a little upgrade.
All of that said, and still - I recommend with all my heart!
BTW - yes, everything in the pictures is vegan! The complete experience of value for money and the quality of the burger is really high.
The deals they offer are very cheap compared to other good burger companies in Tel Aviv and the level of the food isn't lower.
They have some really nice combinations and toppings for the burgers as well which I personally really like.
I would highly recommend trying one of the Port 19 shops at least once", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXCAm9_YEtRJAhIvZD_UfuTYzQC4PgVZcdQ590vpFvPJTl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Itamar Naim', 'publishTime': '2023-09-24T03:53:47.000Z'}, {'text': "The burgers were really tasty, fresh and well cooked, and the fries were perhaps the best I've ever had. They also had English menus as well, as our Hebrew is not very good! Wish we could come back again every night!", 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyN-hgaI17gQY6OmjPBde4QfbrBoOSBvhOU2jcgmBF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Lewis Godfray', 'publishTime': '2023-02-06T22:21:06.000Z'}, {'text': "Great hamburgers, no ketchup or any other abomination inside the meat, lots of tasty variations, pineapple, cheese etc.

Despite having no bun due to dietary restrictions, the meal was satisfying thanks to some additional vegetables instead.

The staff was very nice, the sitting area is spacious and comfortable, however it could use a little more cleaning.

Prices are average, though there is a combo of a burger with a soft drink plus a side dish for about 60 shekels which is quite a good deal.

I loved my time there and would definitely stay there again.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUT3S8KvLzcfPwKtTxHqDNDTjjUQBJ3RlRXG9bd5PstUOhUDQs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Peter Barnett', 'publishTime': '2023-09-16T20:10:14.000Z'}, {'text': 'This place is a little far from the beach but has pretty good access to the city. The rooms are comfortable but could use a curtain or rail for a bit more privacy. The facilities like the lounge and rooftop are a highlight of this stay.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVal0Br5QHq754kj8SPv0OS0z1nrX26J7MVHOP65YJ7DOc5GRM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'authorName': 'Mark Sneddon (Marcosolotravels)', 'publishTime': '2023-09-04T12:27:11.000Z'}, {'text': 'The room was very clean, personell were very nice and service was quick. We asked for a crib and it was brought and installed in less than 15 minutes. The bed are very comfortable and breakfast food fresh and delicious. I forgot my wallet in the room after checkout and the reception contacted me to inform it was found. Location is 2 minutes from  ROTHSCHILD  street.
We had a great experience and we will recommend and return.', 'rating': 5, 'language': 'en', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9NrPDhj5XcEpYPHwjncV8BiN5S8W3Tq8FZm5W9KTfv1VDhD4V=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'authorName': 'Dana Berdugo', 'publishTime': '2023-08-23T15:28:14.000Z'}, {'text': 'It really offers a service of a hostel ++. Donâ€™t expect it to be a hotel.
